 * @section Overview_Section Overview
 *
 * This tutorial shows how to perturb the surface of a 3D model:
 * - 3D model is loaded from a 3D texture,
 * - surface is pertub by a Perlin noise,
 * - a 1D texture color map is used.
 *
 * <br> 
 * The main themes related to volume rendering are :
 * - signed distance field
 * - noise (Perlin noise used to perturb surface)
 * - transfer function (used for color mapping)
 * - color alpha-premultiplication (to avoid color bleeding)
 * - shading model (lambert illumination model)
 *
 * <hr>
 *
